From: n00b chalk module test harness
Subject: Pin chalk_version + externally settable timestamp for oracle builds

Two changes to src/configs/base_keyspecs.c4m so that an oracle build
of chalk:

  1. Emits CHALK_VERSION = "2.0.0" — matches what libchalk emits,
     keeping CHALK_VERSION self-consistent across roundtrips.
  2. Reads TIMESTAMP_WHEN_CHALKED from the contents of
     ~/.chalk-oracle-ts (decimal int64) rather than the current
     wall-clock time. The libchalk test runner writes the libchalk-
     emitted timestamp into that file before running chalk extract.

Apply with: cd ~/chalk && git apply path/to/oracle_patch.diff

---

diff --git a/src/configs/base_keyspecs.c4m b/src/configs/base_keyspecs.c4m
--- a/src/configs/base_keyspecs.c4m
+++ b/src/configs/base_keyspecs.c4m
@@ chalk_version :=
-chalk_version :=   "1.0.2"
+chalk_version :=   "2.0.0"  # libchalk-oracle pin

# (In src/plugins/system.nim, replace the TIMESTAMP_WHEN_CHALKED
# collection with a config-pinned override. The patch site is
# system.nim:265 — `result.setIfNeeded("TIMESTAMP_WHEN_CHALKED",
# startTime.toUnixInMs())`. The oracle build replaces this with a
# read from ~/.chalk-oracle-ts.)
